The death toll has increased several times and is yet to be updated as the number of missing persons in the town of 300 000 inhabitants, located 60 kilometres from the city of Rio de Janeiro, has not yet been established by the Fire Department. According to the Civil Defence Secretariat, 269 landslides and 325 incidents have also been reported this Wednesday. At least 21 people were rescued alive According to the Civil Defence Secretariat this Wednesday, 269 landslides and 325 incidents were also reported. At least 21 people were rescued rescued. The city hall asked the population to avoid leaving their homes. During the early hours of the morning, Civil Defense agents visited some points in the city that were affected by heavy rains. The State Department of Civil Defence believes that between 35 and 50 houses were affected. --ChannelAfrica--